1
00:00:04,823 --> 00:00:09,491
If what makes Kṛṣṇa happy
is breaking my heart,

2
00:00:09,491 --> 00:00:11,300
then that’s my happiness.

3
00:00:11,301 --> 00:00:14,140
[Deep See Diving]

4
00:00:14,601 --> 00:00:16,823
And I told, Śrīla Gurudev,

5
00:00:16,823 --> 00:00:26,025
he could somehow reveal 
these sort of things in a very sweet way,

6
00:00:26,025 --> 00:00:37,384
and also with a little humour,
and triggered by so-called ordinary events.

7
00:00:37,420 --> 00:00:41,820
So, Nietzche says, “There are no facts,
there are just interpretations”,

8
00:00:41,820 --> 00:00:48,183
so it’s not what happens;
the interpretation is everything.

9
00:00:48,183 --> 00:00:52,020
So as we told, Gurudev,
in his final days …

10
00:00:52,020 --> 00:00:56,571
We know how much he loves prasādam
and he cannot take everything;

11
00:00:56,571 --> 00:01:03,777
they’re having to gradually restrict his diet
but they're still cooking so many things,

12
00:01:03,777 --> 00:01:07,999
and sometimes they’re trying to,
in a hidden way,

13
00:01:07,999 --> 00:01:15,532
bring them to us who have the honour
of taking prasādam with Śrīla Gurudev.

14
00:01:15,547 --> 00:01:22,500
And once …. He’s very quiet normally,
when taking prasādam,

15
00:01:22,500 --> 00:01:30,514
but this particular day he starts singing
some song in a very garrulous way,

16
00:01:30,640 --> 00:01:36,308
and so I took the risk of asking him,

17
00:01:36,308 --> 00:01:41,229
“What does that mean? 
The song you’re singing, what is it about?”

18
00:01:41,229 --> 00:01:45,166
And he immediately …
it was like, okay to ask,

19
00:01:45,166 --> 00:01:51,635
and he said, “Oh, Mahārāj, 
Rādhārāṇī is very unhappy.”

20
00:01:51,635 --> 00:01:58,864
Why? He said, “Because, not only is Kṛṣṇa
going to the house of another gopī,

21
00:01:58,900 --> 00:02:03,939
but He’s going through her courtyard.”

22
00:02:03,939 --> 00:02:05,678
What made him think of that?

23
00:02:05,678 --> 00:02:10,310
He’s saying, “This prasādam, 
it’s sad enough that

24
00:02:10,310 --> 00:02:15,699
they’re secretly giving things to you
that they’re not giving to me,

25
00:02:15,853 --> 00:02:18,094
but that they’re walking them
right in front of me

26
00:02:18,094 --> 00:02:23,226
and putting them on your plate 
is too much.

27
00:02:23,548 --> 00:02:26,738
That, I cannot tolerate.”

28
00:02:27,955 --> 00:02:33,226
But that’s his maha-bhāgavata
vision of things;

29
00:02:33,226 --> 00:02:41,315
to see that going on, and he thinks of 
Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa and their divine pastimes,

30
00:02:41,315 --> 00:02:45,856
and this very high thing comes out—
the position of Rādhārāṇī.

